Description: Fragment of oval handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora to sharpish turn. Clay fine pink-buff; cream slip. Circular stamp with rose symbol.
Curator's comments: Name Zenon. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ALEX ABC 0363.33. Trimmed.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0577)
